</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="021BC4E276C13ECA5E63D854E47ACC24" pageId="181" pageNumber="182" type="distinguishing features">
<paragraph id="8ADF057073B6B0DCEE5B3AB4D1718D27" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">Distinguishing features.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="910E2188F62C5335A44516B61C93C30A" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">The type subspecies is characterised by the sessile, sometimes clasping, very acute, sometimes apiculate stem leaves and bracts, long slender inflorescence branches with flowers usually 2 -3 together, the sepals acute and the corolla 8-13 mm long. Spinescent side branches are few or absent.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5317C6B14E5566F15F7D84A2FCF9C43C" pageId="181" pageNumber="182" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8F3592F875839232075C836547BEEBD5" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="20E4D1B563900962B350DC3EC9E86183" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">
Iraq (
<emphasis id="4ABC44CD31B4794EBA3EB17606AAD2BC" italics="true" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">Wheeler-Haines</emphasis>
1127, 
<emphasis id="407D646F2D1D94384A3878D51E4BC6E8" italics="true" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">Rawi</emphasis>
21548; 
<emphasis id="519CF69C41BD8D3779D2CDC30C6AF57C" italics="true" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">Guest et al.</emphasis>
14347, 
<emphasis id="28ADFF0AF4141E80DCB15A3BDE722A4A" italics="true" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">Guest</emphasis>
4016, 4020, 
<emphasis id="F068CF1E76FCF078852510F3FD6BD175" italics="true" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">Rechinger</emphasis>
8072, 9658, 
<emphasis id="D33D6D1748B1589A04DB1673287F39C7" italics="true" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">Barklay</emphasis>
2430, 
<emphasis id="3699A0A028A0709B6EFF01F247DCF964" italics="true" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">Uvarov</emphasis>
s.n. [26/5/1932], 
<emphasis id="4766B26D25B5775B965B923AD1D8A616" italics="true" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">Hazim</emphasis>
30665, 
<emphasis id="E9605395FB394688C2438DE1166E3FA4" italics="true" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">Katib &amp; Tikriti</emphasis>
29735); Iran (
<emphasis id="DF4230BDF06C68FEDD70499B67813FFB" italics="true" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">Haussknech</emphasis>
t s.n. [6/1868]; 
<emphasis id="0DF96C67F575074DB2033A7DBE804210" italics="true" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">
Olivier &amp; 
<normalizedToken id="21FF9FD357D0779D588EBC81DEB6AF11" originalValue="Brugière">Brugiere</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
s.n.); Kuwait (
<emphasis id="11459AD9C65770F11E590D66325495CD" italics="true" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">Dickson</emphasis>
243). Mainly in Iraq.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F48AE17D72F8822A4E6EF7F14AACE46D" pageId="181" pageNumber="182" type="notes">
<paragraph id="C6B78AB2C9798770EDF75AA000213E0F" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EC7BB66BC65E88FEF76F572402B68673" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">
<emphasis id="8836CF095C4B19F43CB7B0EFB2B23C1F" italics="true" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">Rawi &amp; Alizzi</emphasis>
34452 is atypical because of short side branchlets, these and the main branches terminating in slender sharp spines. It is suggested that 
<taxonomicName id="0938C5D17E53097B2CBD8CEED5B22BF5" authorityName="Sa'ad" authorityYear="1967" baseAuthorityName="Rech. fil." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus cateniflorus" order="Solanales" pageId="181" pageNumber="182" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cateniflorus">
<emphasis id="0B5C11619B5EDFFC061A297B11E30262" italics="true" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">Convolvulus cateniflorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from typical 
<taxonomicName id="54036DC6574993860DAA7AF7E8AC6BFB" authorityName="Boiss., Diagn. Pl. Orient. 7: 26. 1846. (Boissier" authorityYear="1846" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus oxyphyllus" order="Solanales" pageId="181" pageNumber="182" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oxyphyllus">
<emphasis id="A5C95F168C6A24A6166AB82E56F4713D" italics="true" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">Convolvulus oxyphyllus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the shorter, less spinescent, more densely tomentose stems and solitary flowers (Rechinger 1964: 483) but all kinds of intermediates can be found.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
